issues.title: Carbon Buildup on Intake Valves
issues.description: Direct injection engines are prone to carbon deposits on intake valves since fuel doesn't wash over them. This affects airflow and engine performance over time.
issues.fix_description: Walnut blasting or chemical cleaning of intake valves, typically required every 60,000-80,000 miles
issues.prevention: Use top-tier gasoline, occasional highway driving, consider periodic intake cleaning additives

issues.title: Turbocharger Wastegate Rattle
issues.description: Wastegate actuator develops excessive play causing rattling noise, especially noticeable at idle or light acceleration.
issues.fix_description: Replace turbocharger wastegate actuator or entire turbocharger unit
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes with proper grade oil, allow engine to cool down after hard driving

issues.title: Paint Defects and Peeling
issues.description: Paint adhesion issues causing peeling, flaking, or bubbling, particularly on hood, roof, and trunk areas.
issues.fix_description: Sand down affected areas and repaint, may require full panel repainting
issues.prevention: Regular washing and waxing, garage parking when possible, avoid harsh chemicals

issues.title: Infotainment System Freezing
issues.description: Mazda Connect system occasionally freezes, becomes unresponsive, or reboots unexpectedly during operation.
issues.fix_description: Software update, CMU replacement if hardware failure, or system reset
issues.prevention: Keep system software updated, avoid using system during extreme temperatures

issues.title: Brake Pad Premature Wear
issues.description: Front brake pads wearing faster than expected, sometimes requiring replacement before 30,000 miles under normal driving conditions.
issues.fix_description: Replace brake pads and resurface or replace rotors if necessary
issues.prevention: Avoid aggressive braking, regular brake inspections, proper break-in of new pads

issues.title: Oil Consumption Issues
issues.description: Some engines consuming excessive oil between changes, potentially leading to low oil levels and engine damage if not monitored.
issues.fix_description: Engine rebuild or replacement, piston ring replacement, valve seal replacement
issues.prevention: Regular oil level checks, use correct oil specification, address issues early

issues.title: Transmission Hesitation
issues.description: Automatic transmission hesitates or delays when shifting, particularly noticeable during acceleration from stops or at low speeds.
issues.fix_description: Transmission software update, fluid change, or transmission rebuild in severe cases
issues.prevention: Regular transmission fluid changes, avoid aggressive driving, warm up before driving

issues.title: Air Conditioning Compressor Failure
issues.description: AC compressor failing prematurely, resulting in loss of cooling capability and potential damage to other AC system components.
issues.fix_description: Replace AC compressor, flush system, replace receiver/dryer and expansion valve
issues.prevention: Regular AC system maintenance, run AC periodically year-round, check refrigerant levels

issues.title: Windshield Stress Cracks
issues.description: Windshield developing stress cracks without apparent impact, typically starting from edges or corners.
issues.fix_description: Complete windshield replacement with proper OEM glass
issues.prevention: Avoid extreme temperature changes, park in shade when possible, address small chips immediately

issues.title: Fuel Pump Failure
issues.description: In-tank fuel pump failing prematurely, causing engine stalling, no-start conditions, or fuel delivery issues.
issues.fix_description: Replace in-tank fuel pump assembly, may require fuel tank removal
issues.prevention: Keep fuel tank above quarter full, use quality fuel, replace fuel filter as recommended

issues.title: Rear Differential Whining
issues.description: AWD models experiencing rear differential whining noise, particularly during turns or under load conditions.
issues.fix_description: Replace rear differential assembly or rebuild with new bearings and seals
issues.prevention: Regular differential fluid changes, avoid aggressive driving, proper tire rotation

editorial.tagline: Premium turbo sedan hiding in plain sight
editorial.hero_blurb: The Mazda6 2.5 Turbo transforms the brand's flagship sedan from pleasant to potent. With 250 horsepower and 310 lb-ft of torque, it finally gives the gorgeous body the punch it always deserved.
editorial.essence: Mazda's sleek sedan gains genuine performance credentials without sacrificing its refined character. The turbocharged engine provides BMW-baiting torque while maintaining the brand's signature driving dynamics and upscale cabin quality.
editorial.heritage: Building on Mazda's third-generation flagship sedan platform introduced in 2012, the turbo variant arrived in 2018 as the spiritual successor to the beloved Mazdaspeed6, albeit in a more mature, luxury-focused package.
editorial.design_philosophy: Mazda pursued 'Kodo' design language excellence with premium materials and craftsmanship, creating a sedan that punches above its price point while delivering the performance the beautiful exterior promised.
editorial.motorsport_history: While this generation lacks direct racing pedigree, it carries the DNA of Mazda's rotary racing heritage and the turbocharged legacy of the beloved Mazdaspeed lineup.
editorial.engine_character: The SkyActiv 2.5T delivers muscular low-end torque with a satisfying whoosh from the turbo, building power smoothly without the peaky nature of smaller displacement turbos.
editorial.transmission_feel: The six-speed automatic prioritizes smoothness over sportiness, with reasonably quick shifts but lacks the crisp manual mode engagement enthusiasts crave.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: G-Vectoring Control subtly manages torque delivery through corners, creating an unusually composed and predictable chassis that rewards smooth inputs over aggressive driving.
editorial.steering_feel: Precise and well-weighted electric steering provides good feedback for the segment, though it lacks the ultimate communication of German sport sedans.
editorial.brake_confidence: Strong, progressive brakes with good pedal feel inspire confidence in spirited driving, though the system prioritizes refinement over outright stopping power.
editorial.sound_signature: Pleasantly muted exhaust with subtle turbo whistle under acceleration, prioritizing cabin refinement over dramatic audio theatrics.
editorial.ideal_owner: Premium sedan buyers seeking German luxury feel without the price tag, who value style, comfort, and surprising performance in equal measure.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Manual transmission enthusiasts, track day warriors, or buyers seeking maximum performance per dollar who don't prioritize luxury touches.
editorial.buyers_summary: Find examples with the premium package for maximum luxury feel. The turbo transforms this sedan from pretty to potent, making it a genuine alternative to entry-luxury sedans at a significant savings.
pros: Genuinely quick acceleration with abundant torque
Premium cabin materials and build quality
Striking exterior design that ages gracefully
cons: Six-speed automatic feels outdated compared to rivals
Rear seat space compromised compared to competitors
best_for: Daily commuting with style and comfort
